{
  "stem": "1473.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember trying to lick the, the, the brandy that-- with which you make Kiddush.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was my, my mother was shomer Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father and his brother-in-law had to keep the store open because things were so bad.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I know they felt badly about that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I think Jewish lore or tradition says that, in order to make a living that one can trespass.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't know if that is so or not.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But my mother was strictly kosher.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it wasn't only that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The holidays were meaningful.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "As I said, I went to Hebrew school and to religious school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I was told that, in my mother's family, there were some distinguished scholars.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My mother's older brother, who was in this country-- that's the uncle who came here in 1933-- was a very pious Jew.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But I loved him because it wasn't the, the letter of the law, which of course he followed, but it was the spirit-- his kindness, his ability to forgive, and yes, it was a very strictly Jewish home.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My father came from a less-observant environment.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] he, he followed whatever.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Of course, he had a-- he had a good Jewish background.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It goes without saying.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Wonderful.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I never was able to stay up for the second part.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] I remember that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father had, also, a beautiful voice.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he sang.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he sang it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I loved it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We had-- of course, we had a double set of dishes for Passover only-- the milchig and the fleishig.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I helped my mother bring down these-- these were the beautiful dishes, not what we used all year but the Pesach dishes.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I remember one set with little, tiny red roses.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
